cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE

The paper deals with neural scene representations and their ability to reason about geometry and appearance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for scene representation that involves deep learning, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses a differentiable ray-marching algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
